<![CDATA[Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.FirstName},<div><br></div><div>Three AMAZING volunteering opportunities coming up this month - get involved!</div><div><br></div><div>1. Volunteer to raise awareness for <u>Coventry Asylum Refuge Action Group</u></div><div><br></div><div>Where: Coventry Peace House&nbsp;</div><div>When: This <b>Saturday 15th March&nbsp;</b>12pm-4.30pm</div><div>What: Help clear up Swanswell Park (used by service users) to make the community a nicer place to live</div><div>Why: Learn about asylum destitution, the Right to Work, improve the park. Plus - you get free food to say thank you!</div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;2. Steward at <u>Coventry Half Marathon</u></div><div><u><br></u></div><div>Where: Coventry City Centre</div><div>When: <b>Sunday 23rd March </b>6.30am-1.30pm</div><div>What: Be part of Decathlon's Half Marathon Team and steward in the runner's village - storing bags, directing runners and cheering them on!</div><div>Why: Amazing atmosphere, all volunteers get a free T-shirt and free entry to next year's half marathon</div><div><br></div><div>3. Sleep rough for a night with <u>Coventry YMCA</u></div><div><u><br></u></div><div>Where: Coventry City Centre&nbsp;</div><div>When: <b>Friday 28th March</b> 7pm-7am</div><div>What: Sleep rough with other volunteers (under cover)</div><div>Why: Raise awareness and money to tackle homelessness in the UK. Food and hot drinks provided, entertainment encouraged! (games, songs, guitars)</div><div><br></div><div>All volunteering events will have The Challenge Society mentors there. Lots of fun and great experience for your CV!</div><div><br></div><div>To sign up or for more info, just email katy.massey@the-challenge.org or text Katy on 07794485976.</div>]]></td>
